glosses: to chop, hash, to cut into slices or pieces; to carve, chop to bits

etymology:
From Ottoman Turkish طوغرامق (doğramak, “to cut up into slices or lumps, to slice, to carve”), from Proto-Turkic *togra- (“to cut into slices, cut into small pieces”).
Cognates
Cognate with Karakhanid [script needed] (toɣrāmāk, “to cut into slices”), Crimean Tatar doğramaq (“to cut into slices”), Azerbaijani doğramaq (“to chop, hack”), Bashkir турау (turaw, “to cut, chop, hack, kill”), Chuvash турама (turama, “to crumble, chop up”), Kazakh турау (turau, “to cut, slice, crumble”), Khakas тоғырирға (toğırirğa, “to cut, chop, crumble”), Kyrgyz тууроо (tuuroo, “to cut into slices”), Southern Altai туураар (tuuraar), Turkmen dogramak (“to cut into pieces”), Tuvan доораар (dooraar, “to cut into pieces”), Uyghur توغرىماق (toghrimaq, “to cut up, chop”), Uzbek toʻgʻramoq (“to cut, mince”).
